GIVEN: http://www.hpmuseum.org/software/41/41quater.htm
q = 2 - 3i + 4j - 7k
Conjugate:
q*= 2 + 3i - 4j + 7k

Reciprocal:
q^-1 = 0.0256 + 0.0385 i  -0.0513 j + 0.0897 k


ONE CAN CONCLUDE THAT:

General:
q =w+xi+yj+zk;

q*=w-xi-yj-zk "conjugate"

||q||=(w^2+x^2+y^2+z^2)^(1/2) "norm" or "magnitude"

q^-1=(w-xi-yj-zk)/(w^2+x^2+y^2+z^2) "reciprocal"

TAKE THAT, HARD AS HELL WIKIPEDIA!
